            <p class="text-[#3c4241] mb-3 lg:text-sm text-xs">You have the right to access and correct personal data being processed by LSU about you. You may access and/or correct your personal data submitted through the online form through the LSU Network, Programs and Computerization Center (NPCC) - Web development via email at 
              
              
            
              <a href="mailto:dev@lsu.edu.ph" class="text-blue-700">dev@lsu.edu.ph</a>.
            </p>
            <p class="text-[#3c4241] mb-3 lg:text-sm text-xs">In order for LSU to ensure that your personal data are disclosed only to you, these offices will require the presentation of your valid government issued ID (GIID) or other IDs or documents that will enable LSU to verify your identity. In case you process or request documents through a representative, in order to protect your privacy, LSU requires you to provide a letter of authorization specifying the purpose for the request of documents or the processing of information, and your LSU ID or other valid GIID, along with the valid GIID of your representative.
                Aside from the right to access and correct your personal data, you have the following rights, subject to the conditions and limitations provided under the DPA and other applicable laws and regulations:</p>
            <p class="text-[#3c4241] mb-3 lg:text-sm text-xs">The right to be informed about the processing of your personal data through this and other applicable privacy notices.</p>
